2026-06-26 00:19:17 [INFO]   PRE-FLIGHT BRIEFING: V1 (RESEARCH DEMO)
2026-06-26 00:19:17 [INFO] ================================================================================
2026-06-26 00:19:17 [INFO] What you are about to see is the foundational cryptographic pipeline:
2026-06-26 00:19:17 [INFO]   1. Setup: The TTP generates 512-bit safe primes, DH keys, and MIFE master keys.
2026-06-26 00:19:17 [INFO]   2. Encryption: Each Smart Meter locally masks its reading using DH shared
2026-06-26 00:19:17 [INFO]      secrets, then applies Functional Encryption (MIFE) and Homomorphic Hashing.
2026-06-26 00:19:17 [INFO]   3. Aggregation: The Gateway (AG) blindly aggregates ciphertexts.
2026-06-26 00:19:17 [INFO]   4. Verification: The Control Center (CC) uses LHH to cryptographically verify
2026-06-26 00:19:17 [INFO]      the aggregate hasn't been tampered with, then decrypts the total sum.
2026-06-26 00:19:17 [INFO]   5. Queries: The CC re-encrypts the aggregate for the Cloud Server
2026-06-26 00:19:17 [INFO]      to evaluate specific functions blindly.
2026-06-26 00:19:17 [INFO] ================================================================================
